# Finnhub REST API key — used only by the Node.js proxy (npm run api).
# Never sent to the browser; never bundled by Vite.
# Get a free key at https://finnhub.io
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your key.
FINNHUB_API_KEY=

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# The variables below are optional and needed only for specific modes.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# VITE_API_BASE_URL — set on Vercel (or your static host) when deploying
# the proxy separately (Mode C). Points the frontend at your deployed proxy.
# This is not a secret — it is a public URL only.
# Leave unset for local development; the frontend defaults to http://127.0.0.1:8787
# Do NOT set VITE_FINNHUB_API_KEY — the Finnhub key must never reach the browser.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-deployed-proxy.example.com

# MARKET_DATA_HOST — bind address for the Node.js proxy.
# Default: 127.0.0.1 (loopback only — safe for local development).
# Set to 0.0.0.0 on a public host (Render, Railway, Fly.io) to accept external connections.
# MARKET_DATA_HOST=0.0.0.0

# MARKET_DATA_PORT — port override for the Node.js proxy.
# Default: 8787. Many platforms (Render, Railway) set PORT automatically.
# The proxy reads MARKET_DATA_PORT first, then PORT, then falls back to 8787.
# MARKET_DATA_PORT=8787

# CORS_ORIGIN — restrict which browser origin may call the deployed proxy.
# In local development, the proxy automatically allows http://localhost:8502
# and http://127.0.0.1:8502 — no setting needed.
# In production (Render, Railway, Fly.io), set this to your Vercel deployment URL:
#   CORS_ORIGIN=https://portfolio-analytics-dashboard-three.vercel.app
# Without this set on a production host, CORS will fall back to localhost origins
# and your deployed frontend will receive a CORS error.
#
# CORS_ORIGIN is NOT a secret. It is your frontend's public URL.
# Do NOT create VITE_FINNHUB_API_KEY — the Finnhub key must never reach the browser.
# FINNHUB_API_KEY belongs only on the proxy host, never in Vercel environment variables.
CORS_ORIGIN=
